item.title: RuneScape HD Deobfuscation
item.dc:creator: @cartridges cartridges
item.description:
@cartridges wrote:

peterbjornx:

i have built an working HD loader with dll support together with light232/God Sent but i still need a deob of HD

HD loader is piss easy.

For a dynamic loader, which is necessary if you intend on making a bot that lasts a a bit longer, just use runtime.loadLibrary(“lib”)… to load the natives into the runtime. You may have to change security settings heh.

However the easier solution is to take a normal loader and have the bootstrap wrap and load the natives… Easy as setting the classpath really.

Hope this helps your efforts!

[hr]

Try doing as ollie stated, jdbg works great… Step, make checkpoints, figure out what stuff does then write an updater to find it each code change until one day you realize you have enough information gathered to move to the next step: creating a system that does something with the information, such as a bot.

item.title: RuneScape HD Deobfuscation
item.dc:creator: @qauters qauters
item.description:
@qauters wrote:

[quote=“Ollie, post:6, topic:223592”]i dont see why its so hard, it took me about an hour to do it all, from research to final build, hey it may not be the best code. but i was going for time not quality in this case, only to prove a point!

the point being “DIY”, all it takes is a retarded brain.[/quote]
People asking for it, can’t deob anything. It’s piss easy to make it compilable again.
Although it’s sad, that jad doesn’t decompile return statements before the catch.
(Like:

try {
   return Class.forName(s);
} catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
   throw new ClassNotFoundException().initCause(e);
}

Would decompile as:

return Class.forName(s);
ClassNotFoundException e;
e;
throw (new NoClassDefFoundError()).initCause(e);

So you have to rewrite it to:

Class c = null;
		
try {
   c = Class.forName(s);
} catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
   throw new ClassNotFoundException().initCause(e);
}
		
return c;

(don’t know about jode on this thing ;))
